article.headline: SE Missouri State 85, Tennessee State 68
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Reggie Golson scored 18 points Saturday night, and Southeast Missouri State extended its winning streak to seven games with an 85-68 victory over Tennessee State. Terrick Willoughby, Dainmon Gonner and Derek Winans added 16 points each for the Redhawks (13-10, 8-4 Ohio Valley Conference. Southeast Missouri State led by 19 points at the half, but had to pull away late after Tennessee State (11-15, 6-6) closed within eight points with just over six minutes left. Bruce Price led Tennessee State with 18 points. Rod Flowers added 16 points, Eric King had 15 and Rashaun Bowens finished with 10.
